title: A Ricardo Oliveros goal eventually lifted U of L to a 2-1 victory over UConn on Tuesday
text:
A Ricardo Oliveros goal in the 72nd minute broke a tie and eventually lifted the Louisville men's soccer team to a 2-1 victory over UConn at home on Tuesday night.
The Huskies (3-5-4) took a 1-0 lead on a goal by Tyler Leeman in the 27th minute. The Cardinals (5-5-3) squared the game with a Daniel Johnson goal in the 40th minute and Oliveros' left-footed strike from 12 yards inside the box proved to be the difference as U of L snapped a four-game winless streak.
The Cardinals take on No. 19 Boston College at 7 p.m. Friday evening at Lynn Stadium.
